A working pyfribidi win32 build project based on pyfribidi
from https://github.com/pediapress/pyfribidi,
http://svn.silentsound.net/pyfribidi/
& fribidi from http://fribidi.org/download/fribidi-0.19.6.tar.bz2

Windows Build
1) Down load the version of fribidi you intend to build from and
untar into this folder. I used fribidi-0.19.6

2) Edit fribidi-config.h to reflect the correct version.

3) run vcvarsall.bat for the C platform you intend building for.

4) either patch the fribidi source directly and run builder.bat
or run the build.vbs script. Both may need editing to reflect changes
in the names of the folders.

5) Assuming 4 worked you now have a configured fribidi source area.
cd to src and make a link to the fribidi folder called
fribidi-src

windows 
   cd src
   junction fribidi-src ../fribidi-0.19.6

linux
   cd src
   ln -s ../fribidi-0.19.6 fribdi-src

6) build/install using the commands
windows 
    python win-setup.py build

linux
    python setup.py build

etc etc.

Good luck.
